AGI - The Moscow attack "was in the air", so much so that "we had warned our compatriots on the site of the Farnesina not to go to Russia and, if on the spot, not to participate in events already on March 8". The Foreign Minister, Antonio Tajani, said this in an interview with Corriere della Sera. "No Italian, from our information, is involved in the attack," Tajani said. "Now we hope that Putin will not exploit a dramatic episode of terrorism to raise tension: we all must commit ourselves to cooperate in the fight against terrorism, so that no more similar episodes can be repeated."
&nbsp;
An act that only concerns Russia? "Terrorism concerns everyone - Tajani replied - is yet another great danger to peace. And we're all willing to cooperate to fight him. Not only because one has to do so that the tension on the Russian eastern front does not rise further, but because the threat can become global. We immediately expressed our solidarity with the victims, we are all on the same side in fighting these terrible actions." &nbsp;
<div </div
Speaking of any risks to Europe and Italy, the Minister added: "Certainly, we can't even lower the guard. The tension in the Middle East, in the Red Sea, the war in Ukraine, led to an increase of controls on all sensitive objectives in our country. The presence of law enforcement and services is constant, even here a few days ago three alleged terrorists linked to the Al Aqsa brigades were arrested at the Eagle. Let's not underestimate anything."
&nbsp;
And on any contacts with the Russian government, the minister continued: "At government level, we obviously have constant contacts with our embassy and our consulates. Of course, relations between intelligence cannot be excluded in these situations, especially with regard to international terrorism. It turns out that the Americans themselves warned Russia of an imminent danger of attacks."
&nbsp;
The argument, Tajani added, will still be on the table of the G7 of Capri in April, and first again to the next NATO summit of foreign ministers immediately after Easter. "It is a theme that concerns international security, on which maximum collaboration is necessary." What can Italy do? "Italy has the opportunity to use international scenarios that see it protagonist in order to favor a peace process that safeguards the freedom and rights of a occupied State like Ukraine and that leads to an end of hostilities. And to do so, in fact, we continue to support Kiev without delay." &nbsp;
