"As for us, we are Europeanists, we work for stability, we want more Europe and we do not want to harm it." The Foreign Minister, Antonio Tajani, said this in an interview with Corriere della Sera, commenting on the statements of the League leader, Matteo Salvini, on Emmanuel Macron and Ursula von der Leyen. "The positioning of our parties in the Union is not part of the government program and does not touch the coalition or stability of the executive, which on international crises has a unique line. We in FI are in the Ppe, and you will see that the Popular will express both the President of the European Parliament and the Commission. We don't argue, some language doesn't belong to us. We believe in Europe, in its foreign policy, in a common defence, in European popularism. Then, every political force is free to make its choices." (AGI)RED
