AGI - Russian forces launched air attacks on Kiev and the western region of Lviv in the early hours of Sunday, according to Ukrainian sources. "Explosions in the capital. Air defense works. Don't leave the shelters," wrote the mayor of Kiev Vitali Klitschko on Telegram. The governor of the Lviv region, Maksim Kozitski, reported missile attacks in the Stryi district, south of the city of Lviv. The Ukrainian army declared that an air alarm was issued throughout the country.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The operating command of the Polish armed forces (RSZ) declared that during the night, an intense activity of long-range aircraft from the Russian Federation was observed. "All the necessary procedures have been activated to ensure the safety of the Polish airspace and the RSZ is constantly monitoring the situation," he said in a statement.
&nbsp;
In recent weeks Russia and Ukraine have intensified reciprocal air bombing. Moscow had done so with the launch of dozens of missiles on Friday and the use of explosive drones against Ukrainian energy infrastructure.&nbsp;
